casebody.data:
DUEBER WATCH-CASE MANUF’G CO., Respondent, v. FAHYS, et al., Appellants. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. March 17, 1893.) Action by the Dueber Watch-Case Manufacturing Company against Joseph Fahys and others.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and O’BRIEN and FOLLETT, JJ.

W. A. Jenner, for appellant. Mr. Oldham, for respondent.

No opinion. Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements. See 22 N. Y. Supp. 69.
